devil's grip
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:a pronounced dip behind sheep's shoulders that allows moisture to drain from fleecewool, preventing rotting of the wool.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
